# Testing Rules

## TDD Red-Green-Refactor
1. Write failing test first (red)
2. Write minimum code to pass (green)
3. Refactor with tests green

## Unit / Integration (Vitest)
- 100% coverage on business logic — no exceptions
- Test file next to source: `Foo.test.tsx` beside `Foo.tsx`
- Use `describe` blocks to group related tests
- Test names: `it('should <behavior> when <condition>')`
- Mock external dependencies (DB, API, email) — test in isolation
- Use `beforeEach` for setup, `afterEach` for teardown — never `afterAll` for state
- Avoid `toBeTruthy` / `toBeFalsy` — assert exact values

## E2E (Playwright)
- Test real user flows, not implementation details
- Use `data-testid` attributes for selectors — never CSS classes
- Each test must be fully independent — no shared state between tests
- Run against a seeded test database — never production
- Screenshot on failure automatically

## Coverage Thresholds
- Statements: 90%+ minimum
- Branches: 85%+ minimum
- Functions: 90%+ minimum
